title: Daniel Day Lewis’ model son Gabriel Kane stuns at Vogue Paris Gala | The
text:
IT SEEMS we have a new up-and-coming celebrity child to look out for — Daniel Day Lewis’ son Gabriel-Kane.
The 20-year-old aspiring model smouldered at the Vogue Paris Foundation Gala this week and got everyone talking about his chic style, strong bone structure - and even his eyebrows.
With a new bleached hairstyle, the oldest son of the three-time Oscar winner rocked a navy blue suit. And he’s clearly inherited his dad’s piercing eyes and chiselled jawline.
He’s definitely inherited his dad’s looks. Source: Instagram
Smoulder. Source: Getty Images
But on top of all of this, it’s his thick, dark eyebrows that have received the most interest — with some thinking they could give Cara Delevingne’s a run for their money.
The day after the Vogue Gala, Gabriel-Kane walked in the Chanel Couture show and later escorted family friend Julianne Moore around the event.
Julianne Moore is a longtime friend of Daniel Day-Lewis. Source: Getty Images
The aspiring model has walked runways at Paris Men’s Fashion Week and been snapped for a number of magazine spreads.
When he was 18, he was also trying to kickstart a rap career under the name “Gabe Day”.
After the Paris Couture show, he Instagrammed a snap of himself posing with models, Rita Ora and Karl Lagerfeld.
“The Chanel Squad. What an amazing show,” he captioned the pic.
“Was so honoured to be a part of it. Posting a few pictures from it soon. Well done to everyone who participated in it.”
'The Chanel Squad' (Frame content direct link: https://instagram.com/p/41e-Fbt7qY/embed .)
Originally published as Hollywood has a new celebrity child to watch out for
